   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Click the Batch System tab at the top of the screen to display the main Batch System screen, shown below.  </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Click the down arrow button to display the popup window to navigate to the following operation screens, which are shown on the following pages:</p>
      <ul class="- topic/ul ">
         <li class="- topic/li ">Scales – monitors the two batch container scales, and the two minors scales.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Status – provides details about the operation of the scales, pan mixer, and other equipment.  </li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Status AGV – monitors the AGV status and position.  This screen is discussed in detail in document SBS-OP-023 Using the SCADA AGV Screen.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Preselection – selects the formula and scale to use for making the next batch.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Formula – Used to enter data for new batch formulas, and to modify existing batch formulas.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Timer Plant – sets the timing values for silo dosing, mixer operation, and pressure settings.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Names – used to assign names and numbers to each batch.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Silo Balance – Not Applicable</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Consumption – shows the amount of material used from each silo over time.</li>
         <li class="- topic/li ">Batch Protocol – provides details on each material in a batch including the weight
            added and its target value, and the start and stop dosing times.</li>
      </ul>
